@startuml
title Turing Platform - ML Experiment Deployment and Execution Control Flow

actor User
participant "Python SDK" as SDK
participant "API Server" as API
participant "Router Manager" as RouterMgr
participant "Experiment Engine" as ExpEngine
participant "Ensembler Manager" as EnsemblerMgr
participant "Kubernetes Cluster" as K8s
participant "Batch Job Manager" as BatchMgr
participant "Spark on K8s" as Spark
participant "Logger Service" as Logger
participant "Alert Manager" as Alert
participant "GitLab (GitOps)" as GitLab
database "BigQuery/Kafka" as Storage
participant "Prometheus" as Prometheus
participant "Jaeger" as Jaeger

== Router Creation and Deployment ==
User -> SDK: Create router configuration
activate SDK
SDK -> API: POST /routers (HTTP/JSON or UPI/gRPC config)
activate API
API -> RouterMgr: Create router instance
activate RouterMgr
RouterMgr -> RouterMgr: Validate configuration
RouterMgr -> K8s: Generate Kubernetes specs (Builder Pattern)
activate K8s
K8s -> K8s: Create router deployment
K8s --> RouterMgr: Deployment created
deactivate K8s
RouterMgr --> API: Router created
deactivate RouterMgr
API --> SDK: Router ID and status
deactivate API
SDK --> User: Router details
deactivate SDK

== Experiment Engine Setup ==
User -> SDK: Configure experiment (A/B test)
activate SDK
SDK -> API: POST /experiments
activate API
API -> ExpEngine: Register experiment runner
activate ExpEngine
ExpEngine -> ExpEngine: Load engine plugin (Factory Pattern)
ExpEngine -> ExpEngine: Initialize runner (Standard/Custom/Planout/Optimizely)
ExpEngine --> API: Experiment engine ready
deactivate ExpEngine
API --> SDK: Experiment configured
deactivate API
SDK --> User: Experiment ID
deactivate SDK

== Ensembler Deployment ==
User -> SDK: Deploy ensembler (PyFunc/Docker/Standard)
activate SDK
SDK -> API: POST /ensemblers
activate API
API -> EnsemblerMgr: Create ensembler
activate EnsemblerMgr
EnsemblerMgr -> EnsemblerMgr: Select ensembler type (Strategy Pattern)
EnsemblerMgr -> K8s: Deploy ensembler service
activate K8s
K8s -> K8s: Create ensembler pods
K8s --> EnsemblerMgr: Service deployed
deactivate K8s
EnsemblerMgr --> API: Ensembler ready
deactivate EnsemblerMgr
API --> SDK: Ensembler endpoint
deactivate API
SDK --> User: Deployment successful
deactivate SDK

== Runtime Request Flow ==
User -> RouterMgr: Incoming prediction request
activate RouterMgr
RouterMgr -> ExpEngine: Get experiment assignment
activate ExpEngine
ExpEngine -> ExpEngine: Evaluate experiment logic
ExpEngine --> RouterMgr: Route decision (treatment variant)
deactivate ExpEngine
RouterMgr -> RouterMgr: Route to model endpoint(s)
RouterMgr -> EnsemblerMgr: Send model predictions
activate EnsemblerMgr
EnsemblerMgr -> EnsemblerMgr: Combine predictions (Strategy Pattern)
EnsemblerMgr --> RouterMgr: Ensembled result
deactivate EnsemblerMgr
RouterMgr -> Logger: Log result (async)
activate Logger
Logger -> Logger: Serialize to protobuf
Logger -> Storage: Write to BigQuery/Kafka/Fluentd
activate Storage
Storage --> Logger: Logged
deactivate Storage
deactivate Logger
RouterMgr -> Jaeger: Send trace data
activate Jaeger
Jaeger --> RouterMgr: Trace recorded
deactivate Jaeger
RouterMgr --> User: Prediction response
deactivate RouterMgr

== Batch Ensembling Job ==
User -> SDK: Submit batch job
activate SDK
SDK -> API: POST /batch-jobs
activate API
API -> BatchMgr: Create batch job
activate BatchMgr
BatchMgr -> BatchMgr: Parse job configuration (YAML)
BatchMgr -> Spark: Submit Spark application
activate Spark
Spark -> K8s: Create Spark driver/executor pods
activate K8s
K8s --> Spark: Pods running
deactivate K8s
Spark -> Spark: Execute batch ensembling
Spark -> Storage: Write results
activate Storage
Storage --> Spark: Write complete
deactivate Storage
Spark --> BatchMgr: Job completed
deactivate Spark
BatchMgr -> API: Update job status
API -> API: Trigger webhook (event-driven)
API --> SDK: Job status
deactivate API
deactivate BatchMgr
SDK --> User: Job result
deactivate SDK

== Alert Configuration ==
User -> SDK: Configure alert rule
activate SDK
SDK -> API: POST /alerts
activate API
API -> Alert: Create alert configuration
activate Alert
Alert -> GitLab: Commit alert rule (GitOps)
activate GitLab
GitLab -> GitLab: Store configuration as code
GitLab --> Alert: Rule committed
deactivate GitLab
Alert -> Prometheus: Register alert rule
activate Prometheus
Prometheus --> Alert: Rule active
deactivate Prometheus
Alert --> API: Alert configured
deactivate Alert
API --> SDK: Alert ID
deactivate API
SDK --> User: Alert active
deactivate SDK

== Monitoring and Logs ==
User -> SDK: Get pod logs
activate SDK
SDK -> API: GET /logs
activate API
API -> K8s: Retrieve pod logs
activate K8s
K8s --> API: Log stream
deactivate K8s
API --> SDK: Logs
deactivate API
SDK --> User: Display logs
deactivate SDK

Prometheus -> RouterMgr: Scrape metrics
activate Prometheus
activate RouterMgr
RouterMgr --> Prometheus: Metrics data
deactivate RouterMgr
Prometheus -> Alert: Evaluate alert rules
activate Alert
Alert -> Alert: Check thresholds
Alert -> User: Send alert notification
deactivate Alert
deactivate Prometheus

@enduml
